Zero Tickets, Zero Wrecks, but Your Rates are Up? Welcome to the NC "Group Project" From Hell.

Remember that one group project in 10th-grade Biology?

You did all the research. You built the diorama. You wrote the paper. But because "Chad" decided to play Snake on his Nokia instead of pasting the labels, the whole group got a C-.

North Carolina auto insurance is starting to feel exactly like that.

We are seeing customers right here in Elkingood folks with perfect driving recordsopening their renewal notices and gasping. Your record is clean. Your car is the same. So why is the price tag suddenly looking like a mortgage payment?

The "Shared Pain" of North Carolina

In the insurance world, we are all in a giant pool together. When the water gets dirty, we all have to swim in it.

Even if you are the safest driver in Surry County, your rate is impacted by state-wide trends. And right now, the trends are ugly. We call it Social Inflation, but you can just call it "expensive."

The Reality: Parts cost more. Labor costs more. And distracted driving is causing more severe accidents than ever before.

Why is the "Class" Failing?

Its not just inflation. Its the severity of the wrecks. Modern cars are computers on wheels. A fender bender that used to cost $500 to fix with a rubber mallet now involves recalibrating sensors, replacing cameras, and three weeks in a specialized shop. That $500 dent is now a $3,500 claim.

When insurance carriers lose money on these massive payouts across the state, they file for rate increases with the NC Rate Bureau. When those get approved, everyones bill goes up. Even yours.
